---
title: Apricot-Glazed Chicken with Couscous & Swiss Chard
description: A double whammy of apricot jam and dried apricot makes for a delightfully sweet and sticky glaze. To balance its sweetness, we're cooking this sauce with savory chicken stock and sharp red onion. Folding tender Swiss chard into hot couscous is a great 2-minute trick for getting more greens in your meals!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5537abe66ced6ec6038b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/5537abe66ced6ec6038b4567.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 687 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 7 g
time required: 40 minutes
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/apricot-glazed-chicken-5537abe66ced6ec6038b4567
servings: 2
---

Halve, peel, and dice half the @red onion{1} into @red onion{1/2}(peeled and diced). Thinly slice the remaining half into @red onion{1/2}(thinly sliced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Finely chop the @parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped). Trim and discard the bottom inch of the @Swiss chard{1%bunch}, then thinly slice into ribbons. Coarsely chop the @dried apricots{1.5%ounce}(coarsely chopped). Cut the @chicken breasts{2} into 1-inch pieces.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the sliced red onion and cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened.

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add the diced red onion to the pot and cook, tossing, ~{3-4%minutes}, until softened. Add @water{1%cup} and @salt{pinch} to the pot and bring to a boil. Once boiling, add the @couscous{1/2%cup}, cover, and remove from heat. Let stand, covered for ~{5%minutes}.

While the couscous cooks, season the chicken with @salt{} and @black pepper{} on both sides, then add to the #pan with the sliced onion. Cook, tossing, until golden brown but not yet cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Stir the Swiss chard and half the parsley into the couscous and cover, about ~{2-3%minutes}, to wilt. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @water{1/2%cup} and the @veggie stock concentrate{1} to the pan with the chicken. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until sauce is reduced by half, about ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @apricot jam{1%tablespoon} and the chopped apricots and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper, if necessary.

Plate the couscous and top with the chicken and apricot mixture. Garnish with remaining parsley and enjoy!